lymphocytic non-lactational mastitis?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Diabetes mellitus","Bacterial infection","Smoking","Recent breast surgery","Oral contraceptive use"],"correctOptions":[0],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EDiabetes mellitus\u003C/strong\u003E, particularly type 1 diabetes is strongly associated with lymphocytic mastitis. The condition is thought to have an autoimmune component and often presents with breast tenderness and firmness.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe incorrect options can be explained:\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EBacterial infection\u003C/strong\u003E is more commonly associated with acute lactational mastitis\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ESmoking\u003C/strong\u003E has not been established as a significant risk factor for lymphocytic mastitis\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ERecent breast surgery\u003C/strong\u003E causes inflammation but is not specifically associated with lymphocytic mastitis\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EOral contraceptive use\u003C/strong\u003E does not increase the risk of developing lymphocytic mastitis\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003C/ul\u003E\u003Cp\u003ELymphocytic mastitis is characterised by lymphocytic infiltration of breast tissue and is often associated with other autoimmune conditions (e.g. primary Sjogren\u0027s syndrome, rheumatoid arthritis, Hashimoto\u0027s thyroiditis)\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["Lymphocytic mastitis is a chronic inflammatory condition of the breast that commonly occurs in patients with diabetes mellitus and autoimmune conditions.","Non-lactational mastitis differs from lactational mastitis in its risk factors, presentation, and management approach."],"references":["Alhabshi SM, Rahmat K, Westerhout CJ, Md Latar NH, Chandran PA, Aziz S. Lymphocytic mastitis mimicking breast carcinoma, radiology and pathology correlation: review of two cases. Malays J Med Sci. 2013 May;20(3):83-7. PMID: 23966831; PMCID: PMC3743988.","Kirby RX, Mitchell DI, Williams NP, Cornwall DA, Cawich SO. Diabetic mastopathy: an uncommon complication of diabetes mellitus. Case Rep Surg. 2013;2013:198502. doi: 10.1155/2013/198502. Epub 2013 Jul 1. PMID: 23936718; PMCID: PMC3713321.","Arulkumaran, S., Ledger, W., Denny, L., \u0026 Doumouchtsis, S. (Eds.). (2019). Oxford Textbook of Obstetrics and Gynaecology. Oxford University Press.","Padubidri, V. G., \u0026 Daftary, S. N. (Eds.). (2014). Shaw\u0027s Textbook of Gynecology E-book. Elsevier health sciences."]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"55895"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"16222"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"55895","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/55895"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2024-12-15T09:42:29+10:30","updatedAt":"2024-12-15T19:06:04+10:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"8913"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"70431"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"67","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/67"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Basic Science","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"5"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"71","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/71"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Junior","synonyms":null,"description":"Suitable for a junior, pre-clinical medical student","position":0,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"6"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"74","links":{"self":"htt